===Etymology 1===
<div style=float:right;>
{{wp|ja:}}
{{wp|Samurai}}
</div>
{{ja-kanjitab|さむらい|yomi=k|alt=士}}
{{IPAfont|⟨sa morapi<sub>1</sub>⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/saburapi/}} → {{IPAchar|/saburafi/}} → {{IPAchar|/samurawi/}} → {{IPAchar|/samurai/}}

Sound shift from ''saburai'' (see below), itself the {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei|pos=stem or continuative form}} of classical verb {{m|ja|侍ふ|tr=saburafu||to [[serve]]|pos=modern ''saburau''}}.

The shift from ''saburaf-'' → ''samuraf-'' is due to the development of the {{m|ja|女性語|tr=josei-go||{{w|Gender differences in spoken Japanese|women's language}}}} in {{w|Middle Japanese}}. A different development of this ''b'' is seen in {{m|ja|候|tr=sōrō||[[service]]|pos=classical ''saurafu''}}.

