=====Usage notes=====
In modern popular usage, the terms ''bushi'' and ''samurai'' are often used in both English and Japanese somewhat loosely to refer to any soldier or warrior during Japan's feudal age (prior to the {{w|Meiji period}}).  In historical contexts, these terms may be used with more specific senses, wherein ''bushi'' refers to any professional warrior, and ''samurai'' refers more strictly to a hereditary social class.  See also {{pedia|Samurai#Terminology}}

